    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // AP7: GENERIC SYNCHRONIZATION — Complex multi-way synchronization
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    //
    // Pattern: Multiple branches synchronize at arbitrary points with complex dependencies
    // Real-world: Orchestration of multiple teams, with inter-dependencies and wait points
    // Example: Product launch → [parallel: design, engineering, marketing] → review → merge
    //
    // Traces show:
    // - Multiple parallel activities starting from different points
    // - Complex dependencies (engineering waits for design, marketing can proceed independently)
    // - Multiple merge points before final completion

